        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the casserole is almost done, trim your <strong>green beans</strong> and add to one side of a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>(use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 7-9 min or until the green beans are tender but retaining a bite and the ciabatta is warm and crusty</p>",
